instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin constellation orchestrates the system’s architectural description across multiple modeling languages and simulation tools within a central MBSE framework.  Component and connector aspects are encoded using architecture description languages such as ACME or AADL, while SysML Interaction Block Diagrams (IBDs) capture functional and logical interactions.  Behavioral detail is embodied either in MontiArc Automata or in SysML v1.7 state machines, and simulation models are integrated via MathWorks Simulink or equivalent tools, allowing the tight coupling of discrete‑time heterogeneous models.  This multi‑notation, component‑centric orchestration provides coordinated resource management by linking the static structural model with its dynamic simulation counterpart, thereby sustaining a coherent end‑to‑end Digital Twin representation."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The Digital Twin lifecycle is delineated by successive abstraction levels: 1) Requirements capturing the functional intent and performance criteria; 2) Functional architecture that defines capabilities and interfaces; 3) Logical architecture that specifies component behaviours and interaction patterns; 4) Product or technical layer that models concrete implementation details and material properties. Transitions between stages are managed via model transformations and conformance checks in SysML specification diagrams (e.g., internal block diagrams, state machine diagrams). Lifecycle governance is achieved through Model‑Based Systems Engineering (MBSE) practices that enforce traceability and versioning across these layers."
]
